  "texts": [
    "First, to align with the Likert scale format conducive to the analysis, modifications were made to the phrasing of original statements.",
    "For example, the general inquiry \"Do you think English is important in the world these days?\"",
    "was transformed into a more assertive statement suitable for a Likert-scale response: \"English is one of the most important languages in the world. \"",
    "This change not only facilitated ease of response but also aligned with the quantitative analysis framework of this study.",
    "Additionally, items that did not directly relate to the core focus of this research, such as those addressing aspects beyond the scope of L2LM, were judiciously excluded."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}